**Serde compatibility note:** Every new field added to existing structs uses `#[serde(default)]` (or `#[serde(default = "fn_name")]` for non-Default types). This ensures all existing serialized data continues to deserialize correctly — no migrations needed.

**Duplicate edge variant note:** Several universal semantic edges (e.g., `SimilarTo`, `RelatesTo`, `DescribedBy`, `Contradicts`) already exist in some pipelines under slightly different names or with the same name. Before adding a variant, check the existing enum. If it already exists with the exact same spelling, skip it. If it exists under a different name (e.g., `DescribesCode` for `DescribedBy`), keep both — the old name for backward compat, the new name for the universal set.
